sleFaultMgmt.name: sleFaultMgmt
sleFaultMgmt.description: The MIB module representing multiple logical entities for the SLE alarm management.

sleFaultNextSeqNum.name: sleFaultNextSeqNum
sleFaultNextSeqNum.description: Sequence number for the alarm synchronization. This value has a number to be used for the next alarm trap.

sleFaultControlRequest.name: sleFaultControlRequest
sleFaultControlRequest.description: This attribute identifies the control commands. updateAlarmList: the NE updates entries of alarms in the sleAlarmListTable after having changed alarm severities of alarms (due to change profile pointers in managed entities or after modification of alarm severities in profiles). This command should be applied once after having finisled modifications of severties. modifyAlarmSeverity: modifies the severity of an alarm in specific profile. createAlarmSeverityProfile: creates a new profile with default severities. The severities then have to be modified with command changeAlarmSeverity. deleteAlarmSeverityProfile: deletes a profile. Profile 1 is not allowed to be deleted. Notifications : none

sleFaultControlStatus.name: sleFaultControlStatus
sleFaultControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

sleFaultControlTimer.name: sleFaultControlTimer
sleFaultControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for command ending. For long running commands. The manager reads this value from the DSLAM.

sleFaultControlTimeStamp.name: sleFaultControlTimeStamp
sleFaultControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sleFaultControlReqResult.name: sleFaultControlReqResult
sleFaultControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sleAlarmSeverityTable.name: sleAlarmSeverityTable
sleAlarmSeverityTable.description: The alarm severity table. The alarm severity table associates profile index and AlarmID pairs with severities to be used for alarm traps. (Note that this table does not apply to cleared alarms).

sleAlarmSeverityEntry.name: sleAlarmSeverityEntry
sleAlarmSeverityEntry.description: Entry of the alarm severity table.
